---
import PublicLayout from '../layouts/PublicLayout.astro'
import { SITE_URL } from '../lib/site'
---
<PublicLayout
  title="Terms of Use — DegreeWiki"
  description="DegreeWiki's terms of use, data accuracy expectations, acceptable use, and limitations of liability."
  canonical={SITE_URL + '/terms'}
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">Last updated: June 2026</p>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">1. About DegreeWiki</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        DegreeWiki is an education information platform for international students. By using
        this site, you agree to these terms. These terms apply to all visitors, whether or not
        you have a DegreeWiki account.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">2. Information accuracy</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        DegreeWiki provides education information for general guidance only. Program details,
        tuition fees, deadlines, admission requirements, scholarship eligibility, visa policies,
        and any other information on this site can change without notice.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Always verify important details — including tuition, deadlines, eligibility requirements,
        and admission conditions — directly with the official university, scholarship provider,
        or government/source website before applying or taking action.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">3. Not professional advice</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Nothing on DegreeWiki constitutes legal advice, financial advice, immigration advice,
        or an official admissions assessment. DegreeWiki is not a university, scholarship
        provider, government agency, legal advisor, or financial advisor.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">4. Fit Finder and AI features</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Fit Finder results and any AI-assisted suggestions are preference-alignment tools.
        They are based on preferences you have saved or on available DegreeWiki context.
        They do not predict or guarantee admission, scholarships, visa outcomes, employment,
        salary, or any other result. Always verify suggested information with the relevant
        official source.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">5. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        You may use DegreeWiki to research education options for personal, non-commercial
        purposes. You may not:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0">&mdash;</span>Scrape or systematically download content without written permission</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0">&mdash;</span>Attempt to access admin areas, private data, or systems you are not authorised to use</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0">&mdash;</span>Use the platform for fraud, impersonation, or any illegal purpose</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0">&mdash;</span>Submit false information through any form or profile on the site</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">6. Accounts</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        You are responsible for maintaining the security of your account credentials.
        DegreeWiki is not liable for unauthorised access to your account resulting from
        your failure to keep your credentials secure.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">7. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        DegreeWiki is provided for general education information purposes. We do not guarantee
        that information on this site is complete, current, or free of errors. We are not
        responsible for any decisions, actions, or outcomes that result from using information
        found on DegreeWiki. Use this site as a starting point for research, not as a
        substitute for official sources.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">8. Changes</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        These terms may be updated as DegreeWiki grows. Continued use of DegreeWiki after
        updates means you accept the revised terms. Significant changes will be reflected in
        the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-gray-100 flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm">
      <a href="/about"      class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">About</a>
      <a href="/privacy"    class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Privacy</a>
      <a href="/disclaimer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Disclaimer</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</PublicLayout>
